PublRem: Covenant Towers is for active individuals & couples 55 & up, It is located in a quiet 9-acre wooded area of old Myrtle Beach just blocks from the ocean &  is adjacent to the Pine Lakes Country Club.  It is the area’s only not-for-profit independent senior living community, every resident not only owns their own spacious condo but a piece of the development. This condo, which is on the top floor (5th) has a great layout with 2 large bedrooms with full bathrooms in each. The master bedroom has a large walk-in closet and the bath has a newly installed custom walk-in bathtub.  There is a full kitchen with recently replaced countertops & appliances. But the gem of this condo is the balcony, as this unit backs up to the woods & off to the right is a pond with a fountain. It is so peaceful & quiet out plus the view is just downright beautiful. I would also be remised if I did not mention that this building is built totally of concrete which provides a very important factor in living in a condo is soundproofing! These are just some examples of the many awesome services that come with ownership in the building; Evening dining in a large dining hall, a coffee shop, a well-stocked library, an outdoor seclude pool, a linen and laundry service, housekeeping, 24-hour security, & a storage locker. Also, every floor has a laundry room. The HOA pays for all utilities in the unit, including cable & internet. Covenant Towers has a full-time activities staff that plans & coordinates recreational activities like Bridge, Bingo, Bowling, Exercise & Yoga, Movies, Music, Golf, Water Aerobics, Lectures & Seminars, Live Shows & Theatre, & Shopping.  Residents may advantage of the free Covenant Towers Shuttles, which go on regular to grocery stores, retail shops, restaurants, open-air shopping such as Broadway at the Beach, Barefoot Landing & Tanger Outlet Malls, & Coastal Grande Mall.
